To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Wisconsin Open Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

On February 6,2023 the Lake Geneva YMCA presented the city council members copies of their plans for a new YMCA  on the recently  city acquired property known as Hillmoor.  The council and mayor were provided copies but the public was not. The city was told to put that presentation on their website but refuses to do so. Requesting all documents in that presentation.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Gary Milliette

title: City of Sausalito Contracts Related to Homelessness Camp Cormorant

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

1.	All FEMA received by the town of Sausalito between in Fiscal years 2020-21, 2021-22, 2022-23.
2.	All Grant agreements by the City of Sausalito for relating to homelessness, the Marinship Park Homeless Encampment in fiscal years 2020-21, 2021-22, and 2022-23 and the State and Federal Government.
3.	All Grant agreements by the City of Sausalito for relating to homelessness, the Marinship Park Homeless Encampment in fiscal years 2020-21, 2021-22, and 2022-23.
4.	The contracts between City of Sausalito and Urban Alchemy.
5.	Urban Alchemy employee conduct protocols on file with the City of Sausalito.
6.	All contracts, and invoices between the City of Sausalito and the law firm called Sheppard Mullin 
7.	All contract, and invoices between the City of Sausalito and the law firm called Kaufman Dolowich & Voluck
8.	All contracts entered by the City of Sausalito with Downtown Streets Team
Regarding the abatement of soil at and around 300 Locust Street in 2021:

9.	The budget, invoices, for the removal of the toxic dirt pile from 300 Locust Street in 2021.
10.	The contract between Ghilloti and the City of Sausalito for removal of the toxic dirt pile from 300 locust street in 2021.
11.	All tests regarding of the above mentioned soil.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Robbie Powelson
